io.smint.clapi.consumer.integration.core.contracts.impl

Class SmintIoBinaryImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.smint.clapi.consumer.integration.core.contracts.impl.SmintIoBinaryImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ISmintIoBinary

    public class SmintIoBinaryImpl
extends Object
implements ISmintIoBinary
    POJO to hold data for binaries.

    In order to provide a downloaded File in getDownloadedFile(), a Provider is being set to this POJO. Using such a provider enables the creator to download the file on first usage only, without the need to download all files in advance although some (all) might not be needed. This POJO implementation does not make use of any cache. So every call of getDownloadedFile() is directly passed to Provider.get(). 

     
     final ISmintIoBinary binaryData = new SmintIoBinaryImpl()
         .setUuid(UUID)
         .setDownloadFile(() -> {
             // NOW CHECK FILE EXISTENCE AND DOWNLOAD IF NECESSARY
             return downloadedFile;
         })

        public File getDownloadedFile()
        Description copied from interface: ISmintIoBinary
        Downloads the binary from Smint.io platform to a temporary file and provides this file.

        The URL to download from is taken from #getDownloadUrl() and all content stored to a temporary file.

        Specified by:
        getDownloadedFile in interface ISmintIoBinary
        Returns:
        an already opened InputStream to read bytes from. If the content type is a textual type, the content is encoded with UTF-8.

        public int getVersion()
        Description copied from interface: ISmintIoBinary
        Get a version number for this binary asset that can be used for updating the asset.

        Comparing the version number of binary assets enables ISyncTarget to detect updates to the binary data. The higher the version number, the more recent the binary data is.

        Specified by:
        getVersion in interface ISmintIoBinary
        Returns:
        a number greater than 0, which is increased by 1 on every update to the binary asset.
